The clinical practice take place at the department of paediatric dentistry. Students deal with the treatment of decidous-, changing and permanent teeth ,oral and dental diseasesObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the practice is to connect theoretical knowledges and practical skills, examine the patient and design a treatment plan and treatment of oral and dental diseases in children. Students work under experienced stomatologists.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  .1. Student knows aetiology, diagnose and treatment about disturbances in mineralisation of the decidious and permanent teeth. 2.Students must be able to diagnose anomalies of dentition, anomalies of teeth form and number. 3. Knows diagnosis and treatment of carious deciduous and permanent teeth. 4.Knows diagnosis and treatment of injuries of deciduous and recently erupted permanent teeth. 5. Different treatment methods of carious complications are used in treating deciduous and permanent teeth of not formed roots. 6.Diagnose and treat periodontitis in children and adolescent. 7.Knows diagnosis and treatment of oral infection diseases in children. 8. Knows the radiographic changes of the teeth. 9. Knows treatment peculiarities of choronic diseases.
